{
  "doc_id": "38246",
  "text": "Previous time series have followed the development of a population on the basis of juvenile cod within a fjord system in the south of Norway by sampling the sites once a year [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , but not to the same extent by collecting adults and egg during the whole spawning period as in the present study. [CITATION_3] evaluated spawning grounds for cod west of Scotland (without DNA sampling), but did not collect egg samples. In our study, we collected egg samples over 3 months in 4 years. Although we observed increased amount of cod eggs (Figure 4) we did not see increased fractions of NEAC ( Figure 6 ). Even though we observe some increase of egg production within the MPA, more research is needed to evaluate whether the number of NCC spawners is really increasing.",
